BIOCASTER ONTOLOGY LICENSE

The BioCaster Ontology is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 Unported
License (see https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode). 

A human-readable version and explanation is available at the Creative Commons website
(http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/). 

For information about how to properly credit data use, please review the Creative Commons
FAQ (https://wiki.creativecommons.org/Frequently_Asked_Questions).

We kindly suggest that you follow standard scientific citation practice if you use the
BioCaster ontology in your publications.  The canonical citation is:

Collier, Nigel, Son Doan, Ai Kawazoe, Reiko Matsuda Goodwin, Mike Conway, Yoshio Tateno, 
Quoc-Hung Ngo et al. "BioCaster: detecting public health rumors with a Web-based text 
mining system." Bioinformatics 24, no. 24 (2008): 2940-2941.

Please contact Nigel Collier (nhc30@cam.ac.uk) for further information.
